div.p:

                           〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                        , &c. I ought not to pass that over in silence, that does yet move me: If any Bishop happen to be angry (as he ought not) and be suddenly or sharply moved against his Priest or Deacon, and would cast him out of his Church, Provision must be made, that he be not condemned being Innocent, or lose the Communion. Let him that is cast out have power to Appeal to the Borderers, that his Cause might be heard, and handled more carefully;


for a Hearing ought not to be denied him when he asks it: And the Bishop, which hath either justly or unjustly ejected him, shall patiently suffer, that the business be lookt into, and his Sentence either confirmed, or rectified, &c.
